</ul>

<h3>Regional Traditions</h3>
<p>Napa's Mediterranean climate produces wines that pair naturally with California cuisine. Think <strong>grilled salmon with avocado salsa</strong>, where the wine's minerality complements the fish while standing up to rich avocado, or <strong>Santa Maria-style tri-tip</strong> with its signature red oak smoke that mirrors the wines' barrel influences.</p>

<h3>Everyday Versatility</h3>
<p>For casual dining, Napa Chardonnay works beautifully with <strong>roasted chicken and seasonal vegetables</strong>, while a Napa Valley red blend adapts to everything from <strong>barbecue brisket to mushroom pizza</strong>.</p>

<h3>Special Occasions</h3>
<p>Celebrate with <strong>prime rib and Yorkshire pudding</strong> alongside reserve Cabernet, or pair vintage Napa Chardonnay with <strong>lobster thermidor</strong> – the wine's oak and richness matching the dish's decadent preparation.</p>

